==Quarterfinals==
The first legs were played on 20 April 2001. The second legs were played on 2 May 2001.

{{TwoLegStart}}
{{TwoLegResult|[[FC Shakhtyor Soligorsk|Shakhtyor Soligorsk]]|| 3–6 |'''[[FC Dinamo Minsk|Dinamo Minsk]]'''|| 1–3 | 2–3 }}
{{TwoLegResult|[[FC Gomel|Gomel]]|| 3–5 |'''[[FC Belshina Bobruisk|Belshina Bobruisk]]'''|| 2–2 | 1–3 }}
{{TwoLegResult|'''[[FC Rechitsa-2014|Vedrich-97 Rechitsa]]'''|| 4–0 |[[FC Torpedo Mogilev|Torpedo-Kadino Mogilev]]|| 2–0 | 2–0 }}
{{TwoLegResult|'''[[FC Slavia Mozyr|Slavia Mozyr]]'''|| 3–3 ([[Away goals rule|a]]) |[[FC BATE Borisov|BATE Borisov]]|| 0–2 | 3–1 }}
|}

==Semifinals==
The first legs were played on 10 May 2001. The second legs were played on 18 May 2001.

{{TwoLegStart}}
{{TwoLegResult|[[FC Dinamo Minsk|Dinamo Minsk]]|| 1–2 |'''[[FC Slavia Mozyr|Slavia Mozyr]]'''|| 0–1 | 1–1 }}
{{TwoLegResult|'''[[FC Belshina Bobruisk|Belshina Bobruisk]]'''|| 1–1 ([[Away goals rule|a]]) |[[FC Vedrich-97 Rechytsa|Vedrich-97 Rechytsa]]|| 0–0 | 1–1 }}
|}

