r 12 & 13, 2015: FIS AS World Cup #8 in {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Åre Ski Area]], [[Jämtland]] *** Women's Slalom winner: {{flagicon|SVK}} [[Petra Vlhová]] *** Women's Giant Slalom winner: {{flagicon|USA}} Lindsey Vonn ** December 16 – 19, 2015: FIS AS World Cup #9 in {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Val Gardena]] *** Men's Super G winner: {{flagicon|NOR}} Aksel Lund Svindal *** Men's Downhill winner: {{flagicon|NOR}} Aksel Lund Svindal ** December 16 – 19, 2015: FIS AS World Cup #10 in {{flagicon|FRA}} Val-d'Isère #2 *** Women's Alpine Combined winner: {{flagicon|SWI}} Lara Gut *** Women's Combined Disciplines Downhill winner: {{flagicon|USA}} Lindsey Vonn *** Women's Downhill winner: {{flagicon|SWI}} Lara Gut ** December 20, 2015: FIS AS World Cup #11 in {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Courchevel]] *** Women's Giant Slalom winner: {{flagicon|AUT}} [[Eva-Maria Brem]] ** December 20 & 21, 2015: FIS AS World Cup #12 in {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Alta Badia]] *** Men's Giant Slalom winner: {{flagicon|AUT}} Marcel Hirscher *** Men's Parallel Giant Slalom winner: {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Kjetil Jansrud]] ** December 22, 2015: FIS AS World Cup #13 in {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Madonna di Campiglio]] *** Men's Slalom winner: {{flagicon|NOR}} Henrik Kristoffersen ** December 27 – 29, 2015: FIS AS World Cup #14 in {{flagicon|ITA}} [[Santa Caterina di Valfurva]] #1 *** Men's Downhill winner: {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Adrien Théaux]] ** December 28 & 29, 2015: FIS AS World Cup #15 in {{flagicon|AUT}} [[Lienz]] *** Women's Giant Slalom winner: {{flagicon|SWI}} Lara Gut *** Women's Slalom winner: {{flagicon|SWE}} [[Frida Hansdotter]] * '''January''' ** January 1: FIS AS World Cup #16 in {{flagicon|GER}} [[Munich]] *** ''Events cancelled.'' ** January 5 & 6: FIS AS World Cup #17 in {{flagicon|ITA}} Santa Caterina di Valfurva #2 *** Men's Slalom winner: {{flagicon|AUT}} Marcel Hirscher *** Women's Slalom winner: {{flagicon|NOR}} [[Nina Løseth]] ** January 7 – 10: FIS AS World Cup #18 in {{flagicon|AUT}} [[Altenmarkt im Pongau|Altenmarkt–Zauc