{{refimprove|date=December 2016}}
{{National rugby union | unionname = Algerian Rugby Federation (FAR) | nativename = | logo = Algerian Rugby Federation (logo).png | logosize = | founded = November 17, 2015 | IRB = | region = [[Rugby Africa]] | regionyear = 2015 | president = Sofiane Abdelkader Benhassen | coach = Salim Tebani | womenscoach = | countryflag = Algeria | url = }}
The '''Algerian Rugby Federation''' (FAR)<ref>{{lang-ar|الفدرالية الجزائرية للرغبي}}</ref> is the governing body for [[rugby union in Algeria]]. Algeria became a full member of [[Rugby Africa]] in December 2016.<ref name="General Assembly 2016">{{cite press release | url=http://www.rugbyafrique.com/general-assembly-2016 | title=General Assembly 2016 | publisher=Rugby Afrique | accessdate=15 December 2016}}</ref> The federation is responsible for the [[Algeria national rugby union team|Algerian national team]] and the Algerian Rugby Championship.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.aps.dz/sport/31774-apr%C3%A8s-43-ans-d-absence,-le-rugby-revient-en-alg%C3%A9rie | title=Après 43 ans d'absence, le rugby revient en Algérie | publisher=Soltani Saadi | work=[[Algeria Press Service]] | date=November 18, 2015 | language=French}}</ref> It is in charge of promoting the sport in Algeria, organizing international matches for the national team, as well as is involved in educating and training players and officials. Algeria have never participated in the [[Rugby World Cup]] qualifiers. Their best result to date is 50-0 wins against [[Egypt]] and [[Libya]],{{citation needed|date=December 2016}} both in a Cairo international tournament in 2010.
==History== During the French presence in Algeria before 1962, rugby union had its followers either in [[Oran]], [[Guelma]], [[Algiers]] or [[Annaba]] where clubs like Stade Oranais, RIJA, USMMC, AGVGA or ES Guelma were existent. Rugby had its moments of glory{{according to whom|date=December 2016}} and many Algerian players have been able to achieve successful professional careers abroad, especially in France;{{vague||date=December 2016}} but discipline disappeared after the independence of Algeria due to lack of multiple items till 1972 when it disappeared completely.
During the beginning of the 2000s, The Algerian Rugby Clubs Committee was established to revive the discipline before creating the federation. On 17 November 2015 the federation was created in [[Algiers]] during a constitutive general assembly chaired by [[Mustapha Larfaoui]], honorary president of the [[Algerian Olympic Committee|Algerian Olympic and Sports Committee]] and attended by representatives of 18 clubs of 16 wilayas. Sofiane Benhassen was elected first president of the federation.
