{{Infobox National Olympic Committee | title = Belize Olympic and Commonwealth Games Association | logo = | size = 150px | country = Belize | code = BLZ | created = 1968 | recognized = 1968 | association = PASO | headquarters = [[Belize City, Belize]] | president = [[Hilberto Martínez]] | secretary general = [[Allan Sharp]] | website = [https://www.olympic.org/belize www.olympic.org/belize] }} '''Belize Olympic and Commonwealth Games Association''' (IOC code: '''BLZ''') is the [[National Olympic Committee]] representing [[Belize]]. It is also the body responsible for Belize's representation at the [[Olympic Games]].
== History == Belize Olympic and Commonwealth Games Association was founded in 1968 and recognised by the [[International Olympic Committee]] in the same year.
