'''Palais des Sports''', known also as the '''Palais des sports [[Pierre Mendès France|Pierre Mendes]]<ref>[http://en.structurae.de/structures/data/index.cfm?id=s0014602 Pierre Mendès France Sports Palace]</ref>''' or "Le Stade Olympique de Glace" is an indoor [[ice hockey]] [[arena]], located in [[Paul Mistral Park]] in [[Grenoble]], [[France]]. The vaulted roof structure was built from November 1966 to April 1967, therefore having tough weather problems to add to construction difficulties. The stadium was conceived for the Olympiques Winter Games held in Grenoble in 1968 and has a capacity of up to 12,000 spectators.

==Events==
The [[Figure skating at the 1968 Winter Olympics|figure skating]] events and some [[Ice hockey at the 1968 Winter Olympics|ice hockey]] games at the [[1968 Winter Olympics]] were held at this arena<ref>[http://www.la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1968/or1968.pdf 1968 Winter Olympics official report.] pp. 108-11. {{en icon}} & {{fr icon}}</ref> called for the event ''Stade de glace''.

The arena hosted the 1972 (3rd) [[European Athletics Indoor Championships]] over 11 and 12th March, the arena was featured on the medals awarded (pictured)
 [[File:Silver medal of the 1972 European Athletics Indoor Games, Grenoble, France.jpg|thumb|Silver 2nd place medal. 11-12 March 1972]]

The arena hosted the 1979 [[SuproLeague|FIBA European Champions Cup]] final<ref name="KK BOSNA">[http://www.eurobasket.com/Bosnia/basketball.asp?NewsID=157032 KK BOSNA marks 30th Anniversary of winning European Champion title]</ref><ref name="Champions Cup 1978-79">[http://www.linguasport.com/baloncesto/internacional/clubes/c1/C1_79.htm Champions Cup 1978-79]</ref> in front of a crowd of 15,000,<ref name="KK BOSNA"/><ref>[http://www.euroleague.net/item/21130 1979: Bosna starts a true dynasty]</ref> the 1983 final of the same competition<ref name="Champions Cup 1982-83">[http://www.linguasport.com/baloncesto/internacional/clubes/c1/C1_83.htm Champions Cup 1982-83]</ref> and also the 1985<ref name="Cup Winners’ Cup 1984-85">[http://www.linguasport.com/baloncesto/internacional/clubes/c2/C2_85.htm Cup Winners’ Cup 1984-85]</ref> and 1988 [[Saporta Cup|Cup Winners' Cup]] final.<ref name="Cup Winners’ Cup 1987-88">[http://www.linguasport.com/baloncesto/internacional/clubes/c2/C2_88.htm Cup Winners’ Cup 1987-88]</ref>

==Structure==
Le structure consists of two crossing cylinders (95m by 65m). The double shell structure (6&nbsp;cm thick) is a hyperbolic paraboloid which transfers the weight down its four resting points. In plan, the structure appears to be a square. At each corner is a 48m cantilever.

