The '''Reaves Arena''' is an 8,250-seat multi-purpose [[arena]] in [[Perry, Georgia]], [[United States|USA]]. It was opened in 1990, hosting local sporting events and concerts. The arena is named in honor of Representative [[Henry L. Reaves]] (D-Quitman) who, along with Representative Larry Walker, was instrumental in the creation of the [[Georgia National Fairgrounds and Agricenter]], where the arena is located. <ref>{{cite web|title=Official Code of Georgia Annotated Volume 42A|publisher=State of Georgia|page=1198|date=2009|accessdate=December 27, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=New Georgia Encyclopedia|publisher=University of Georgia Press|url=http://www.georgiaencyclopedia.org/articles/business-economy/georgia-national-fairgrounds-and-agricenter|accessdate= December 27, 2016|}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Hon. Henry L. Reaves (GA SH 178)|publisher=Georgia House of Representatives|date=2000|url=http://www.legis.ga.gov/Legislation/Archives/19992000/house/gash178.htm| accessdate=December 27, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=In the Beginning|publisher=Georgia National Fairgrounds & Agricenter|url=http://www.gnfa.com/our-history/|accessdate=December 27, 2016}}</ref>
