'''Rules''' is an [[Athletics (sport)|athletic game]] played between two players, on a 64 foot square grid. It is characterized by its use of sticks similar to that of a stringed instrument [[Bow (music)|bow]], with the aim of getting one's tip through the other stick's space between the slack (the hair) and the rod (the wood).

==Gameplay==
The field consists of 16 squares, called cells, with sides of 2 feet arranged in a square. The players start in diagonally opposite squares in the middle. Every 20 seconds, the players must switch into an adjacent cell. A [[Tally marks|tally]] runs for 20 minutes in this fashion: 3 tallies making a game. One's goal is to strike their stick through the other's stick, whilst simultaneously preventing their own from being struck. However, the two participants must always be facing each other, and cannot move their stick behind their body.

[[Category:Athletic sports]]

{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Sports Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Cleethorpes]], [[Lincolnshire]] | establishment = 1961 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = | end1 = Daggett Road End | end2 = Chichester Road End | year1 = 1984 | club1 = [[Minor Counties cricket team|Minor Counties]] | year2 = <small>1980-1984 1990, 1995, 1997 & 2003-2004</small> | club2 = [[Nottinghamshire County Cricket Club|Nottinghamshire]] | year3 = 1972 | club3 = [[Minor Counties North]] | year4 = 1969-present | club4 = [[Lincolnshire County Cricket Club|Lincolnshire]] | date = 18 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/418.html Ground profile }}
The '''Sports Ground''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Cleethorpes]], [[Lincolnshire]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1961, when Lincolnshire Colts played Derbyshire Juniors.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/418_misc.html Other matches played on the Sports Ground]</ref>
In 1969, [[Lincolnshire County Cricket Club|Lincolnshire]] played their first [[Minor Counties Championship]] match at the ground against [[Staffordshire County Cricket Club|Staffordshire]]. From 1969 to present, the ground has hosted 25 Minor Counties Championship matches<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/418_minc.html Minor Counties Championship Matches played on the Sports Ground]</ref> and 6 [[MCCA Knockout Trophy]] matches, the last of which came in 2002 when Lincolnshire played the [[Leicestershire Cricket Board]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/418_mint.html Minor Counties Trophy Matches played on the Sports Ground]</ref>
The ground has hosted a number of [[first-class cricket|first-class]] matches, the first of which came in the 1980 [[County Championship]] when [[Nottinghamshire County Cricket Club|Nottinghamshire]] played [[Worcestershire County Cricket Club|Worcestershire]]. A combined [[Minor Counties cricket team|Minor Counties]] team played a single first-class match at the ground in 1985 against the touring [[Zimbabwe national cricket team|Zimbabweans]]. Between 1980 and 1990, Nottinghamshire played 4 first-class matches at the ground, including the final first-class match to date at the ground which came against the touring [[Sri Lanka national cricket team|Sri Lankans]] in 1990.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/418_f.html First-Class Matches played on Sports Ground]</ref>
The ground has also played host to [[List-A cricket|List-A]] matches. The first List-A match saw [[Minor Counties North]] play Nottinghamshire in the 1972 [[Benson and Hedges Cup]]. Nottinghamshire have played 5 List-A matches at the ground, including the final one to date to be held at the ground, which came against [[Durham County Cricket Club|Durham]] in 2004. Lincolnshire have also used the match for a single List-A match, which came in the [[2000 NatWest Trophy]] when they played [[Lancashire County Cricket Club|Lancashire]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/418_a.html List-A Matches played on the Sports Ground]</ref>
In local domestic cricket, the Sports Ground is the home venue of [[Cleethorpes Cricket Club]] who play in the [[Yorkshire ECB County Premier League]].<ref>[http://www.cleethorpescricketclub.co.uk/Cleethorpes_Cricket_Club/Home.html Yorkshire Premier League Matches played on Sports Ground]</ref>
